    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9386ebb1_67e922e7",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 152,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-22T00:36:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I haven\u0027t looked at all the code, but it seems like all of the calls to TempGitRepo will now be serialized, so there\u0027s no need for a worker pool.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 152,
        "startChar": 51,
        "endLine": 152,
        "endChar": 77
      },
      "revId": "72862ecc9c8714d6ee019b11132a19872611c2e9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fd61dd00_1380bc43",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 152,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-25T18:10:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "They aren\u0027t truly serialized; TaskScheduler.updateUnfinishedJobs could be running at the same time as TryJobIntegrator.getJobToSchedule.  I just changed this temporary initial setup to run GetOrCacheRepoState for each unfinished job in a separate goroutine, and changed to run TryJobIntegrator.getJobToSchedule to run in multiple goroutines as well.  It\u0027d be nice to find a way to do the same in gatherNewJobs as well, but it\u0027s not immediately clear to me how to make that work.",
      "parentUuid": "9386ebb1_67e922e7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 152,
        "startChar": 51,
        "endLine": 152,
        "endChar": 77
      },
      "revId": "72862ecc9c8714d6ee019b11132a19872611c2e9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0cd660de_6b98afa0",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 152,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-26T02:57:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In gatherNewJobs, you\u0027d have to run RecurseAllBranches once to gather all the cache misses, then populate the cache, then run RecurseAllBranches again to create the missing jobs. IMO it\u0027s rare enough that we have multiple commits coming in on the same cycle that the extra complication doesn\u0027t seem worthwhile.",
      "parentUuid": "fd61dd00_1380bc43",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 152,
        "startChar": 51,
        "endLine": 152,
        "endChar": 77
      },
      "revId": "72862ecc9c8714d6ee019b11132a19872611c2e9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
